A team of US scientists used DNA testing to trace poached elephant tusks, aiming to combat the illegal ivory trade.
They identified China's growing economy as a key driver of the black-market ivory trade, emphasizing the need for strict enforcement and education.
The recent seizure of a large ivory shipment highlights the urgency of the situation, with Kenya and Mali proposing a complete ban on elephant tusks trade.
Despite differing opinions on ivory trade, efforts are being made to address the issue, including proposals for contraception and culling to manage elephant populations and combat poaching.
